</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC717108E5FFFF8DE8EF9F6FA1EE8AA" blockId="6.[151,1437,1407,1873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="3089B4258E5FFFF8DE8EF9F6FA1EE8AA" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
- Pronotum laterally without spine, at most with very small denticle; minimum distance between eye margins equal to ½ of scape length; underside of thorax with sparse, small punctures; free margin of clypeal lobe with barely noticeable notch; tibiae largely dark.............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E5FFFF8DAABF92BFA1EE8AA" authority="(Eversmann)" baseAuthorityName="Eversmann" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[1202,1436,1675,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E5FFFF8DAABF92BFA99E8AB" box="[1202,1307,1675,1697]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">L. camelus</emphasis>
(Eversmann)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308C0FB58E5FFFF8DE8EF90FFA1EE91E" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<paragraph id="8BC717108E5FFFF8DE8EF90FFA1EE8D7" blockId="6.[151,1437,1407,1873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="3089B4258E5FFFF8DE8EF90FFA1EE8D7" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
3 Mesopleuron coarsely and densely punctate, interspaces hardly visible; flagellomere I 2.0 × as long as wide.................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E5FFFF8DAE3F961FA1EE8D7" authority="(Panzer)" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1797" box="[1274,1436,1734,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alata">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E5FFFF8DAE3F961FAC7E8D0" box="[1274,1349,1734,1755]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">L. alata</emphasis>
(Panzer)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC717108E5FFFF8DE8EF944FA1EE91E" blockId="6.[151,1437,1407,1873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="3089B4258E5FFFF8DE8EF944FA1EE91E" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">- Mesopleuron with sparse distinct punctures more than one diameter apart, interspaces smooth and shiny; flagellomere I 1.8— 2.0 x as long as wide................................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308C0FB58E5FFFF8DE8EF8B9FA1EE95A" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<paragraph id="8BC717108E5FFFF8DE8EF8B9FA1EE93F" blockId="6.[151,1437,1407,1873]" box="[151,1436,1821,1844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="3089B4258E5FFFF8DE8EF8B9FA1EE93F" box="[151,1436,1821,1844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
4 Flagellomere I at least 2.5 × as long as wide, II clearly longer than III.................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E5FFFF8DA41F8B9FA1EE93F" authority="(F. Morawitz)" baseAuthorityName="F. Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1112,1436,1822,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluschtschevskyi">
